-- ‘Man of Steel’ Generates $9 Million in Midnight Ticket Sales
-- B y   A n t h o n y   P a l a z z o
-- 2013-06-14T16:14:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-14/-man-of-steel-generates-9-million-in-midnight-ticket-sales.html
“Man of Steel,” Time Warner Inc.’s
reboot of the Superman movie franchise, took in $9 million in
midnight screenings, Hollywood.com-Box Office said.  With $12 million in corporate group-rate showings
yesterday, the film’s U.S. and Canadian ticket sales total $21
million,  Paul Dergarabedian , president of Hollywood.com’s box-office research division, said in an e-mailed statement, citing
the Warner Bros. film unit.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anthony Palazzo in Los Angeles at 
